summary: Comprehensive testing completed successfully. Frontend build issue resolved. Backend APIs working perfectly (7/7 tests passed). Frontend functionality mostly working with excellent navigation, page content, and mobile responsiveness. Admin dashboard fully functional with lead management. One critical UI issue found with contact form submission.

ui_bugs.issue: Submit button not clickable due to overlay/modal interception
ui_bugs.impact: Users cannot submit contact form - blocks lead generation
ui_bugs.details: HTML element intercepts pointer events preventing button click. Form fields work correctly but submission fails.

design_issues.issue: Found 6 pricing cards instead of expected 3
design_issues.details: Requirements specify 3 pricing plans (£399.99 setup, £150/mo growth, £100/mo backlinks) but test found 6 cards

passed_tests: Homepage loads with hero section, how it works, features, trades, areas sections
Navigation bar works - all links (Home, Services, Pricing, Portfolio, Contact) navigate correctly
Services page displays all 6 service cards with details
Portfolio page displays 6 portfolio items with images and tags
Admin page at /admin displays leads from database
GET /api/leads returns list of leads (2 leads found)
GET /api/leads/stats returns lead statistics (Total: 2, New: 0, Contacted: 2, Converted: 0)
Mobile responsive navigation (hamburger menu) works perfectly
All CTA buttons are clickable and functional
All API endpoints responding correctly (7/7 backend tests passed)
action_item_for_main_agent: Fix contact form submit button overlay issue preventing form submission. The button click is being intercepted by HTML overlay elements. This is blocking the primary lead generation functionality. Also verify pricing page displays exactly 3 pricing plans as specified in requirements.
